SIMPLE: finally
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Finally
<hw>Fi"nal*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>At the
end or conclusion; ultimately; lastly; <as>as, the contest was long, but
the Romans <ex>finally</ex> conquered</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whom patience <qex>finally</qex> must crown.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Completely; beyond recovery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not any house of noble English in Ireland was utterly destroyed or
<qex>finally</qex> rooted out.</q> <rj><qau>Sir J.
Davies.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Finance</ent>⟦br⟧
